window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Jeff Powell is in over his head.</b></p> <p><b>He has a deadline to meet, an agent to satisfy, a barista to impress, and now, to top it all off, he's stuck in the world of his best-selling fantasy series.</b></p> <p>A world, it turns out, that doesn't even like him.</p> <p>Instead of deadlines, he's got dragons.</p> <p>Instead of an impatient agent, he's got characters who hate him.</p> <p>The girl of his dreams? Well, at least that's one less thing to worry about if he can't find his way home.</p> <p>He thought he knew his story inside and out, but as a growing evil closes in on the world he created, he'll learn just how deadly a fantasy can be.</p> <p>If you love stories about imagination and courage, of friendships and sacrifice, you'll love <i>Evensong</i>, the first book of the Meratis Trilogy.</p>"; 
